assistantMessages:
I'll place a limit long order for 0.5 ETH at $3,000 on GMX V2. Let me walk through the steps.

## Step 1: Set Up the SDK

```typescript
const { GmxSdk } = require("@gmx-io/sdk");
const { createWalletClient, http } = require("viem");
const { privateKeyToAccount } = require("viem/accounts");
const { arbitrum } = require("viem/chains");

const account = privateKeyToAccount(process.env.PRIVATE_KEY);

const sdk = new GmxSdk({
  chainId: 42161,
  rpcUrl: "https://arb1.arbitrum.io/rpc",
  oracleUrl: "https://arbitrum-api.gmxinfra.io",
  subsquidUrl: "https://gmx.squids.live/gmx-synthetics-arbitrum:prod/api/graphql",
  account: account.address,
  walletClient: createWalletClient({
    account,
    chain: arbitrum,
    transport: http("https://arb1.arbitrum.io/rpc"),
  }),
});
```

## Step 2: Resolve Market & Token Addresses

```typescript
const { marketsInfoData, tokensData } = await sdk.markets.getMarketsInfo();

// Find the ETH/USD perpetual market (WETH index, not spot-only)
const ethUsdMarket = Object.values(marketsInfoData).find(
  (m) => tokensData[m.indexTokenAddress]?.symbol === "WETH" && !m.isSpotOnly
);

if (!ethUsdMarket) throw new Error("ETH/USD market not found");

const marketAddress      = ethUsdMarket.marketTokenAddress;
const collateralAddress  = ethUsdMarket.longTokenAddress;  // WETH — standard collateral for longs
const usdcAddress        = Object.values(tokensData)
                             .find((t) => t.symbol === "USDC")?.address;

if (!usdcAddress) throw new Error("USDC not found");

console.log("Market:     ", marketAddress);
console.log("Collateral: ", collateralAddress, "(WETH)");
console.log("Pay token:  ", usdcAddress, "(USDC)");
```

## Step 3: Calculate the Pay Amount

You want **0.5 ETH** of position size at **$3,000** trigger price:

- Position size = 0.5 ETH × $3,000 = **$1,500 USD**
- For a 1x position (no leverage), collateral = $1,500 → **1,500 USDC**

```typescript
// 0.5 ETH position size at $3,000 = $1,500 notional
// Using 1x leverage: pay 1,500 USDC as collateral
const PAY_AMOUNT_USDC = 1_500_000_000n; // 1,500 USDC (6 decimals)
const LEVERAGE        = 10_000n;        // 1x (10,000 basis points)

// Limit price: $3,000 scaled to 30 decimals
const LIMIT_PRICE = 3_000n * 10n ** 30n; // 3000000000000000000000000000000000n
```

> **Adjust leverage** if you want more size per dollar of collateral — e.g., `50_000n` for 5x gives 0.5 ETH exposure with only $300 USDC collateral.

## Step 4: Place the Limit Long Order

```typescript
const tx = await sdk.orders.long({
  marketAddress,
  payTokenAddress:       usdcAddress,       // Pay with USDC
  collateralTokenAddress: collateralAddress, // Hold WETH as collateral
  payAmount:             PAY_AMOUNT_USDC,
  leverage:              LEVERAGE,
  limitPrice:            LIMIT_PRICE,        // Triggers when ETH <= $3,000
  allowedSlippageBps:    100,                // 1% slippage tolerance
  skipSimulation:        true,
});

console.log("Limit order submitted:", tx);
```

## What Happens Next

| Step | Description |
|------|-------------|
| **Order created** | Your order sits in the GMX order book on-chain |
| **Trigger condition** | Executes when the ETH oracle price drops to **≤ $3,000** |
| **Keeper execution** | A keeper picks it up and fills at the oracle price (within your slippage) |
| **Position opened** | You'll hold a 0.5 ETH long with WETH collateral |

## Key Parameters Summary

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Market | ETH/USD perpetual |
| Direction | Long |
| Order type | Limit Increase |
| Pay amount | 1,500 USDC |
| Leverage | 1x |
| Position size | ~0.5 ETH ($1,500 notional) |
| Trigger price | ≤ $3,000 |
| Slippage | 1% |

> **To cancel** this order later if it hasn't filled:
> ```typescript
> const { ordersInfoData } = await sdk.orders.getOrders({ marketsInfoData, tokensData });
> const orderKeys = Object.keys(ordersInfoData);
> await sdk.orders.cancelOrders(orderKeys);
> ```

